{
  "stem": "6777.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Number two, the Jewish gymnasium taught Hebrew and usually religion and all this subject, where in the Polish gymnasium, you haven't had it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 109,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, the Hasidic community, they used to wear these long, black frocks and the little--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Curls or whatever you call it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they stood out from the rest of the [? people. ?] And especially if they did well.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of them, not all, some had been very, very poor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there have been a few successful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that always made for jealousy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there have been also quite good relationships.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember one of my, my uncle, [INAUDIBLE] he was a president of the town, though that was not anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He went once or twice a year to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he had some friends who would have been Jews, because Kalisz was a spot for the flour mills.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there has been one or two-- at least two which I remember-- as a Jewish flour millers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father, first of all, had an another mill near Berlin and another one in Danzig, which is Gdansk today.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he read all the German papers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember him saying, das [? wort ?] Hitler [? heisst ?] [? krieg-- ?] the word Hitler means war, though he knew exactly what's happening-- what was happening.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 116,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 116,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, my father lost his great fortune, stopped being the millionaire fairly early, because he could not look after the three mills in different-- oh, and there was another rice mill as well-- in the different places.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 116,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He couldn't be in all places at the same time, though he hired some people and they let him down.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
